OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FFirms in four-day week     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ftrial will make it         
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fpermanent                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Many UK firms taking part in a four-day
OL,6, working week trial have said they will 
OL,7, keep it in place after the pilot ends. 
OL,9,FMore than 70 firms are taking part in  
OL,10,Fthe scheme where employees get 100% pay
OL,11,Ffor 80% of their normal hours worked.  
OL,13,FAt the halfway point in a six-month    
OL,14,Ftrial, data shows that productivity has
OL,15,Fbeen maintained or improved at the     
OL,16,Fmajority of firms.                     
OL,18,FThough some "old-fashioned" companies  
OL,19,Ftaking part in the trial had found the 
OL,20,Fshift to a four-day week "trickier".   
